     <h2>Technical Analysis</h2>
    <p>
Technical Analysis is the study of price movement to understand how markets behave.
Instead of focusing on a company’s financials, it analyzes how price reacts to
supply, demand, and trader psychology.
</p>

<p>
At the core of technical analysis is the price itself — and every price movement
can be broken down into four key values, known as <strong>OHLC</strong>.
</p>

<p>
<strong>OHLC</strong> represents how a price behaved during a specific time period:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Open:</strong> The price at which the asset started trading</li>
  <li><strong>High:</strong> The highest price reached during the session</li>
  <li><strong>Low:</strong> The lowest price reached during the session</li>
  <li><strong>Close:</strong> The price at which the asset finished trading</li>
</ul>


<p class="text-muted">
Technical analysis is not about prediction — it is about probability and risk management.
</p>
