  <h2>Volume</h2>

  <p>
    Volume plays a crucial role in technical analysis as it helps confirm
    price movements and market trends. While price shows direction,
    volume reflects the strength behind that move.
  </p>

  <p>
    It represents the total number of shares traded during a specific
    time period. Higher volume indicates strong market participation,
    whereas low volume signals weak interest or uncertainty.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Price up + High volume:</strong> Strong and healthy trend</li>
    <li><strong>Price up + Low volume:</strong> Weak move, possible reversal</li>
    <li><strong>Breakout with high volume:</strong> Higher chance of continuation</li>
    <li><strong>Price down + High volume:</strong> Strong selling pressure</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-muted">
    Volume helps you understand market conviction and validates
    candlestick patterns, trends, and breakouts.
  </p>
