  <h2>Support & Resistance</h2>

  <p>
    Support and resistance are key price levels where a stock tends to
    pause, reverse, or consolidate. These levels are formed due to
    repeated buying and selling behavior in the market.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Support</strong> is a price level where demand is strong enough
    to prevent further decline, while <strong>Resistance</strong> is where
    selling pressure stops the price from moving higher.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Support:</strong> Acts as a price floor where buyers enter</li>
    <li><strong>Resistance:</strong> Acts as a price ceiling where sellers dominate</li>
    <li><strong>Breakout above resistance:</strong> Indicates bullish strength</li>
    <li><strong>Breakdown below support:</strong> Signals bearish momentum</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-muted">
    Support and resistance work best when combined with volume and
    candlestick patterns for confirmation.
  </p>
