      <h2>Indicators</h2>

      <p>
        Indicators are mathematical tools derived from price data that help
        confirm trends, momentum, and potential reversals.
      </p>

      <p class="text-muted">
        Indicators work best when combined with price action and volume.
      </p>

      <h4 class="mt-4">Moving Averages</h4>
      <p>
        Moving Averages smooth price movement to show the overall market direction.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>SMA:</strong> Average price over a fixed period</li>
        <li><strong>EMA:</strong> Gives more weight to recent prices</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Price above MA indicates strength; below MA indicates weakness.
      </p>

      <h4 class="mt-4">Bollinger Bands</h4>
      <p>
        Bollinger Bands indicate market volatility using upper and lower bands
        around a moving average.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Overbought:</strong> Price near the upper band</li>
        <li><strong>Oversold:</strong> Price near the lower band</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="mt-4">Relative Strength Index (RSI)</h4>
      <p>
        RSI measures momentum to identify overbought and oversold conditions.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Overbought:</strong> RSI above 70 indicates buying exhaustion</li>
        <li><strong>Oversold:</strong> RSI below 30 indicates selling exhaustion</li>
      </ul>

